The paper deals with the problem of gathering anonymous agents in a network, which is a classic problem in distributed computing. The paper provides a complete solution to the problem in arbitrary networks, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the leader election problem for anonymous agents in graphs, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Cryptography) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes two universal deterministic gathering algorithms, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
